description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE: INTERNAL APPILCANTS ONLY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 Macmillan Review Radiographer Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; **This post also attracts a 5% Recruitment and Retention allowance** &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part Time: 22.5 hours per week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Following a departmental restructure, funding has been secured for a dedicated Review Radiographers’ team within the Radiotherapy department. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post will be part of this new team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for the development and expansion of our current Review service and associated clinics to ensure the best patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main focus will be to provide and coordinate a patient-focused information and support service for patients referred for radiotherapy at all stages of the Radiotherapy pathway, including referral, pre-treatment, treatment and follow up. This will include providing telephone contact to provide expert advice on radiotherapy side effects and their management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to have good communication skills as they will be required to interact effectively with all staff associated with the patients&#39; care, whilst the patients are undergoing their radiotherapy treatment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates will be expected to work across both our Radiotherapy sites in Reading and Bracknell.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paula Horne (Radiotherapy Service Manager) on 0118 322 7868 or paula.horne@royalberkshire.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
